Flamboyant DStv Premiership side Royal AM are said to be flirting with the possibility of employing new personnel in most departments in a bid to bolster their team’s performance. READ ALSO: Ralani not your average dribbling wizard, says Mokwena “The idea is to have former players who have excelled in their positions and they (Royal AM) want to add them into the technical team to focus on those specific positions. For example, players like Mbulelo Mabizela and Shuan Bartlett could be roped in as a defensive and striker’s coach respectively because those roles need attention much like every team has a goalkeeper coach,” said a source. Head coach John Maduka has been allegedly asked to present a list of names for the club to consider. Royal AM’s chief executive officer, Sinky Mnisi was unreachable for comment.